# CLAUDE.local.md (example)

This is an optional file for your own local rules. It is yours. Template updates never
touch it, so anything you put here is safe to keep across upgrades.

It does nothing while it is named `CLAUDE.local.md.example`. To turn it on, copy it to
`CLAUDE.local.md` in this same folder. Once that file exists, it is loaded at session
start and its rules extend and override the base `CLAUDE.md` for the whole session.

Use it for standing rules you want the agent to follow every time. Keep each rule short
and dated so you can see when you added it and why.

## Rules

- 2026-01-01: always do X when Y
